        public java.lang.String write()
                       throws DeserializationStrategyMissingException
        Writes out the contents of the Serial in a format that it can reconstruct a Serial object from at a later date. The String returned will contain the necessary newlines with added tabbing for increased readability.
        Returns:
        Full string
        Throws:
        DeserializationStrategyMissingException - If during writing there is no strategy available for a class contained within the data of the Serial, the write will fail.
